                            <comment id="15544870" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 4 Oct 2016 09:23:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user mxm opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2586&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2586&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4732&quot; title=&quot;Maven junction plugin security threat&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-4732&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-4732&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; remove maven junction plugin&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    On Windows, the plugin may download code from the author&apos;s web&lt;br/&gt;
    site. The downloaded file is not signed in the same way as Maven&lt;br/&gt;
    artifacts from Maven central which have to be signed with the&lt;br/&gt;
    developer&apos;s key. This could be a potential target for attackers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can merge this pull request into a Git repository by running:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    $ git pull &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mxm/flink&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/mxm/flink&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4732&quot; title=&quot;Maven junction plugin security threat&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-4732&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-4732&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternatively you can review and apply these changes as the patch at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2586.patch&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2586.patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To close this pull request, make a commit to your master/trunk branch&lt;br/&gt;
with (at least) the following in the commit message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This closes #2586&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;commit dcdac00a0432f66bbf2992c8cfcc502d41a7d8c2&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Maximilian Michels &amp;lt;mxm@apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2016-10-04T09:12:35Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4732&quot; title=&quot;Maven junction plugin security threat&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-4732&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-4732&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; remove maven junction plugin&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    On Windows, the plugin may download code from the author&apos;s web&lt;br/&gt;
    site. The downloaded file is not signed in the same way as Maven&lt;br/&gt;
    artifacts from Maven central which have to be signed with the&lt;br/&gt;
    developer&apos;s key. This could be a potential target for attackers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;</comment>
