release-1.1: a31a22ec7fc08cce8da4e5e97010d1b2cf8124e7&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15545403" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 4 Oct 2016 13:54:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user mxm commented on the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2586&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2586&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Merged to `master` and `release-1.1`.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    @uce I also like the symbolic link. I contacted the maintainer of the plugin because it wouldn&apos;t be hard to fix this nowadays with Java 7+ which supports the creation of symbolic links. I think the lack of this was the reason why the author chose to download a binary. However, I don&apos;t know why he didn&apos;t simply ship it with the jar which should have been possible.&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
